{# === 7. Risks in Your DNS — denser text grid, no cards/icons/tool links.
       Reframed (TASK-028) from a second four-card grid into concrete failure
       scenarios. The four tool destinations the old section linked to are
       reachable via the nav Tools dropdown + footer Free Tools column. #}
<twig:SectionContainer bgClass="bg-base-200/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <twig:SectionHeader
            eyebrow="Risks in your DNS"
            title="What Sendvery catches that nobody else does"
            lede="The silent failure modes that break email authentication weeks before anyone notices."
        />
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-10 gap-y-8">
            <div>
                <div class="text-xs font-mono text-base-content/50 mb-1">DKIM</div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-base-content mb-1">Key expired after a DNS migration</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">Your provider rotated DKIM keys but the new selector never landed in DNS. Every transactional email has been silently failing authentication for weeks — Sendvery flags it on the next report.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="text-xs font-mono text-base-content/50 mb-1">SPF</div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-base-content mb-1">Record crept over the 10-lookup limit</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">Each new sender adds an include directive. Once you cross 10 DNS lookups, the entire SPF record is treated as permerror — receivers reject mail without telling you.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="text-xs font-mono text-base-content/50 mb-1">Alignment</div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-base-content mb-1">Marketing tool added to SPF without DKIM</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">SPF passes (the IP is authorised) but DKIM is missing (the sender doesn't sign on your behalf). DMARC alignment fails. Mail lands in spam from a "trusted" sender.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="text-xs font-mono text-base-content/50 mb-1">Subdomain</div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-base-content mb-1">Subdomain inherits weaker policy than apex</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">Your apex domain is on <code class="font-mono text-xs">p=reject</code>, but `mail.yourdomain.com` has no DMARC record — it inherits the apex's <code class="font-mono text-xs">sp=</code> tag (or `p=none` if absent), opening a spoofing window.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</twig:SectionContainer>

